@node "Intro" "Introduction To SCSIPrefsMUI"

                             SCSIPrefsMUI
                             Version  1.0

                          By Joshua B. Helm
                      (C)1995 Yankee Ingenuity


SCSIPrefsMUI is a preferences editor for the A3000 and A3000T build-in SCSI
controller (A3091).  It allows the user to change the stored configuration of
the controller.  These settings are read at reset and the controller
configures itself accordingly.  There are many user-configurable options on
the A3091, however Commodore saw fit NOT to include a standard Prefs program
to alter these setting with the A3000/A3000T; thus the need for SCSIPrefsMUI!

SCSIPrefsMUI is an MUI application and REQUIRES MUI installed on your system.
             
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation Of SCSIPrefsMUI"
Installation of SCSIPrefsMUI is very simple and straightforward.  Be sure you
have a fully functional version of MUI installed before you attempt to use
this program.

 Installation (Sorry, no installer)
 ------------

Extract the archive to a temporary location (RAM: is good):

   LHA x SCSIPrefsMUI.lha RAM:         (Where RAM: is the temp. location)

Copy the program and its icon to its final destination.  SYS:Prefs is
recommended so as to keep your preferences programs together.  The included
icon is a MagicWB prefs style icon.

   COPY SCSIPrefsMUI SYS:Prefs         (Where SYS:Prefs is the)
   COPY SCSIPrefsMUI.info SYS:Prefs    (location you chose    )

Copy the documentation (this file) and its icon to its final resting place:

   COPY SCSIPrefsMUI.guide#? SYS:Prefs (Same applies here too)

 -----------------

That's about it...  You should be all set.  You can run the program by double
clicking the icon, or running it from command line.              
@endnode

