@node "LUN" "Allow LUN Usage"
@toc "Usage"
If this box is checked, it will cause the controller to attempt to access
logical units above 0 at all SCSI addresses.  This may cause a problem with
drives that lock up when LUNs other than 0 are used, or with drives which
respond to ALL LUNs on a device number.

Stored In: Amiga Only Portion

Default After 'Amnesia': Off        
@endnode

@node "ID" "SCSI Host ID"
@toc "Usage"
This gadget sets the SCSI ID of the controller.  The default is usually best
because most SCSI devices can not go that high.  Should you need to change
this setting, you can.

Stored In: Shared Portion

Default After 'Amnesia': 7        
@endnode

@node "SyncXfers" "Synchronous Transfers"
@toc "Usage"
If this box is checked, the SCSI controller will initiate synchronous
transfers rather than waiting for the drive to initiate them.  Use of this
option can result in a sizable speed increase.  Problems can occur with
devices that lock up when a synchronous transfer is attempted, most notably
the Toshiba 3401B CDROM drive.

Stored In: Shared Portion

Default After 'Amnesia': Off          
@endnode

@node "FastSync" "Fast Synchronous Transfers"
@toc "Usage"
This checkbox enables a high speed version of synchronous transfers
(>5MB/sec).  Note that this option has no effect if @{" Synchronous " link "SyncXfers" 0} transfers
are not enabled; thus this gadget becomes disabled.

Stored In: Shared Portion

Default After 'Amnesia': On           
@endnode

@node "Queues" "SCSI-2 Queues"
@toc "Usage"
Activation of this checkbox causes the controller to use SCSI-2 tagged
queuing.  This allows the devices to accept and reorder multiple read/write
requests.

Stored In: Shared Portion

Default After 'Amnesia': Off      
@endnode

@node "Timeout" "SCSI Bootup Timeout"
@toc "Usage"
This gadget adjusts the length of time the SCSI controller should wait for
devices to come online at reset.

 Short:  128ms
 Long:   2secs

This is generally used for older drives which do not respond to selection
until they are fully spun up.

Stored In: Amiga Only Portion

Default After 'Amnesia': Short          
@endnode

@node "Amnesia" "Amnesia Fix"
@toc "Usage"
This gadget allows the user to select how SCSIPrefsMUI should fix the
'Amnesia' state.

 Both:   Fix both the Amiga only and the shared portions.
 Amiga:  Repair only the Amiga portion.
 Shared: Fix only the shared portion.
 None:   Don't fix either, leave them alone.

Note that the other settings are still saved even if the 'Amnesia' state is
not repaired.  The next time you run SCSIPrefsMUI you will be presented with
the warning messages again, indicating that they have not been fixed.  This
gadget is only enabled if the system indicates that it has suffered
'Amnesia'.

Stored In:  Both Amiga and shared portions

Default After 'Amnesia': 'Amnesia' has occured       
@endnode

@node "Save" "Save Button"
@toc "Usage"
Pressing the Save button causes SCSIPrefsMUI to save your new settings and
exit.           
@endnode

@node "Cancel" "Cancel Button"
@toc "Usage"
Presing the Cancel button causes SCSIPrefsMUI to exit without saving your new
settings.  Pressing the window close gadget has the same effect.         
@endnode

@node "About" "About Menu Item"
@toc "Usage"
Selecting the About option from the menu causes SCSIPrefsMUI to bring up a
beautiful window full of wonderous information about the program.  This is a
must see!      
@endnode

@node "Quit" "Quit Menu Item"
@toc "Usage"
This menu option has the same effect as pressing the @{" Cancel " link "Cancel" 0} button or the
close gadget.       
@endnode

